answerBox.snippet: 1989 P Quarter Value Circulated specimens can generally only cost you their face value. However, the 1989 Washington quarters in the mint state don't have a high price either. You can find pieces graded between MS 60 and MS 65 for $1 to $10. If you have a specimen ranked MS 66, you can sell it for any amount $175.
